<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words With W Not Followed By Vowel — Unusual Scrabble Patterns</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">Most players assume W always needs a vowel after it — WA, WE, WI, WO. But Scrabble rewards knowing exceptions. WR words (WRACK, WRING, WRY), W-ending words (BOW, DEW, JAW), and the exotic CWM break this "rule" and give you plays opponents don't expect.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">W + Consonant Patterns</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
    <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">WR- (W before R)</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WRACK (14), WRATH (11), WRECK (14), WREN (7), WRING (9), WRIST (8), WRITE (8), WRONG (9), WRY (9)</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
    <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">-W Endings (W at end)</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BOW (8), COW (8), DEW (7), JAW (13), MEW (8), NEW (6), OW (5), RAW (6), SAW (6), VOW (9), YEW (9)</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
    <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">-WN Endings</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BROWN (10), CLOWN (10), CROWN (10), DOWN (8), FROWN (11), GOWN (8), GROWN (9), SHOWN (11), TOWN (7)</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
    <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Exotic: CWM</p>
    <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CWM (10 pts) — a cirque or valley bowl. No vowel at all! One of Scrabble's rarest valid patterns from Welsh.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scorers (W Without Following Vowel)</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
    <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
      <tr>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Word</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Points</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Pattern</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Notes</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WRACK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3">WR-</td><td class="px-4 py-3">W(4)+R+A+C(3)+K(5)</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WRECK</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3">WR-</td><td class="px-4 py-3">W(4)+R+E+C(3)+K(5)</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">JAW</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">13</td><td class="px-4 py-3">-W</td><td class="px-4 py-3">J(8)+A+W(4)</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">FROWN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3">-WN</td><td class="px-4 py-3">F(4)+R+O+W(4)+N</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">CWM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3">No vowel</td><td class="px-4 py-3">C(3)+W(4)+M(3) — zero vowels!</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">CROWN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3">-WN</td><td class="px-4 py-3">C(3)+R+O+W(4)+N</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">WRY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3">WR-</td><td class="px-4 py-3">W(4)+R+Y(4) — no vowel!</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CWM is the ultimate surprise:</span> At 10 points with no vowel and only 3 tiles, CWM is perfect for tight boards where vowel access is limited. Most opponents will challenge it — and lose their turn.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">W-ending words for parallel plays:</span> -OW, -AW, -EW endings let you place W at the end of a row, creating multiple crosswords. BOW parallel to an existing word can score 15+ points easily.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WRY needs no vowels at all:</span> W(4)+R(1)+Y(4) = 9 points using zero traditional vowels. Combined with CWM, these are your lifelines when vowels run dry.</p>
  </div>
</div>

